text:
Magic Story Update:
Hour of Eternity comes. Eternals arrive. People die brutally.
So it's just zombie Blue Man Group wrecking havok?
Basically. Mostly random people getting slaughtered. One person fighting for a loved one, one to protect others, one trying to redeem his failures, and another accepting it as Bolas' plan.
What is Bolas' plan? What exactly is he trying to achieve?
The specifics haven't really been revealed yet. Bolas has only been present for like 4 paragraphs total so far.

The general idea is pretty solid though: tezzeret hijacked Rashmi's planar portal from Kaladesh, which can transport nonliving matter between planes. 

Nicol bolas has been using Amonkhet as a zombie farm. That's why the training groups are called "crops." They compete in the Ultimate Ninja trials. The weak get embalmed. The strongest warriors are eternalized, covered with lazotep, which removes them from the "living matter" category, so they can be transported through Rashmi's planar gate. Then Nicky B and The Strongest Zombies in the Multiverse (tm) can go on tour
so it's just a coincidence that the planar portal was invented exactly in time for his return set into motion however long ago?
Seems a crazy inefficient way to build an army. What happens when you loose soldiers? How do you replace them.
It's hinted in the story if not said that Bolas can control the rate of the sun. So if that's the case, Bolas can reap the soldiers when he has the portal.

They're eternalized now, so the presumption is that they're significantly difficult to stop. They're dead, after all, but not like Lili's zombies, shambling and brainless. They've retained all their prior combat skills and magical abilities. 28 days later zombies vs night of the living dead, basically
Sure but there's a finite number and they aren't making any more babies.
So he has a pretty badass army, and he can go places and presumably do some conquering. Is that the plan, or is it hinted that this is just the first step in something
proque no los dos

In the art book, it also put a twist of the five trials as five aspects of soldiers that Bolas wanted.
Solidarity = Tactical
Knowledge = Adaptable
Strength = Resilient
Ambition = Ruthless
Zeal = Fanatical

I moved from the small town where I was born prior to kindergarten to another small town like half an hour away. At some point during show and tell or something kids were talking about being born or hospitals or whatever and how all the kids in my class were born in the same hospital in town except me. There was a big-ass hospital in my home town whose name I knew, so I said that was the one where I was born, assuming it must be it being a kindergartner and all. That hospital of course was the state mental hospital.
The kids obviously didn't know that's what it was, but the teacher would have
There's like 20 foot razorwire fences around the building to this day, but as a 5 year old I just knew hospital. Just assumed that must be it.
THAT is how you set expectations low with your kindergarten teacher; tell her you were born in a mental hospital
Hoooo boy! That's a hell of a thing
